EXPLAIN select distinct 1 from t2 a, t2 b where a.c1 = b.c1 limit 1, 1;
Query Plan
=====================================================
|ID|OPERATOR             |NAME|EST.ROWS|EST.TIME(us)|
-----------------------------------------------------
|0 |LIMIT                |    |0       |5           |
|1 |└─LIMIT              |    |1       |5           |
|2 |  └─HASH JOIN        |    |1       |5           |
|3 |    ├─TABLE FULL SCAN|a   |2       |3           |
|4 |    └─TABLE FULL SCAN|b   |1       |3           |
=====================================================
Outputs & filters:
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([1]), filter(nil), rowset=16
      limit(1), offset(1)
  1 - output(nil), filter(nil), rowset=16
      limit(1), offset(nil)
  2 - output(nil), filter(nil), rowset=16
      equal_conds([a.c1 = b.c1]), other_conds(nil)
  3 - output([a.c1]), filter(nil), rowset=16
      access([a.c1]), partitions(p0)
      is_index_back=false, is_global_index=false, 
      range_key([a.__pk_increment]), range(MIN ; MAX)always true
  4 - output([b.c1]), filter(nil), rowset=16
      access([b.c1]), partitions(p0)
      is_index_back=false, is_global_index=false, 
      range_key([b.__pk_increment]), range(MIN ; MAX)always true
select distinct 1 from t2 a, t2 b where a.c1 = b.c1 limit 1, 1;
+---+
| 1 |
+---+
+---+
